subSubSection.paragraph:
It should be noted that Hesse’s first initial is given as “M.” in his publications, but that this stood for “Monsieur”, as his given name was Charles Eugène Hesse (see
Delamare Deboutteville 1965
) and he was an amateur zoologist. For reasons unexplained, he is most often cited in copepod publications (e.g.,
Özdikmen 2008
) as “E. Hesse” (a usage which never appeared in any of his papers). Hesse should be cited in bibliographies as “Hesse, [C. E.]”, as this is the most accurate form.
